<sec id="id-31538fc1-c284-4a49-bcb9-c8f89fde4893"><title><bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="6c145f46-9194-4e56-d78e-1a1e3c5272d0" timestamp="1666104731912"?>Professional equality index<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="6c145f46-9194-4e56-d78e-1a1e3c5272d0"?></bold></title><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="0c225077-aead-4d6f-a41a-d10d2c745944" timestamp="1666104739648"?><bold>(Former box 4)</bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="0c225077-aead-4d6f-a41a-d10d2c745944"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="c0e2957e-5e99-4002-fb1a-227ad3178993" text="All companies from a country with at least 50 employees are required to calculate and publish their professional gender equality index every year on March 1st." timestamp="1668679383418"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="79bb0637-47fd-4365-ee1b-370c1394d932" timestamp="1668679436292"?>In some countries companies with at least 50 employees are required to calculate and publish their professional gender equality index every year in the context of International Womenâ€™s Day.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="79bb0637-47fd-4365-ee1b-370c1394d932"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="26446c30-b76f-4b02-a272-dc2f155f9ec7" timestamp="1666104725028"?>This 100-point index is calculated according to four or five indicators, depending on whether the company has more or fewer than 250 employees:<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="26446c30-b76f-4b02-a272-dc2f155f9ec7"?></p><list list-type="dash"><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="747e0eba-f6ab-4195-9c96-976baeab61d6" timestamp="1666104725028"?><list-item id="id-9113d936-344e-4459-c1db-b99c1e1604f4"><p>the pay gap between men and women;</p></list-item><list-item id="id-75294038-fb6a-49ce-c2c3-fe5ef0ca6f11"><p>the difference in the breakdown of individual pay rises;</p></list-item><list-item id="id-4a646d35-cb42-47d1-b109-43523aa937ce"><p>the difference in the breakdown of promotions (only in companies with more than 250 employees);</p></list-item><list-item id="id-4e568272-aba9-4932-e801-881a583a8291"><p>the number of female employees who receive a pay rise on their return from maternity leave;</p></list-item><list-item id="id-15ab7fba-8578-4d89-b883-fd7170dd0cfc"><p>parity amongst the 10 highest-paid employees.</p></list-item><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="747e0eba-f6ab-4195-9c96-976baeab61d6"?></list><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="0062aa5b-4f1d-471d-fb07-40c9cb32c645" timestamp="1666104725028"?>If the index is below 75 points, the company <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="0062aa5b-4f1d-471d-fb07-40c9cb32c645"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="0695e1bd-59fc-4fef-b21a-f91974629191" text="is required " timestamp="1668694970439"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="313624a6-8e67-47fb-eeed-e39244f6db8d" timestamp="1668694973767"?>should <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="313624a6-8e67-47fb-eeed-e39244f6db8d"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="b17ead55-c73b-48a5-a54c-866175b1762e" text="to " timestamp="1668694976459"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="8b67d61e-27a5-4eac-e374-6d8a597f68c1" timestamp="1666104725028"?>take corrective measures to achieve a score of at least 75 points within three years.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="8b67d61e-27a5-4eac-e374-6d8a597f68c1"?></p><p/></sec>